<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 06 at 4:56PM EDT until May 06 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR SOUTHEASTERN HALIFAX COUNTY
WILL EXPIRE AT 500 PM EDT...
The storm which prompted the warning is starting to move out of the
area. Therefore, the warning will be allowed to expire.  However
small hail is still possible as another strong thunderstorm moves
northeast through the area.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for central North
Carolina.</description>
